{
  "stem": "4967.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Used to go around, the cart, every morning in the ghetto and pick up the dead people, from here, from there, and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the ghetto still gets smaller.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They still take away people for-- for liquidation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And in this Jewish hospital, I was told, that the doctors were very good doctors.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Actually, one of the doctors, Dr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], was a eye specialist, and I knew him before the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we came to Germany, he was in the same camp with me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And people tried-- tried to give their children what they still had in the ghetto to the peasants of Lithuania, which a few did, maybe a few dozens, gave their children for money, for gold to hide out.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I know cases that after the war, the non-Jewish people who hide out, who brought up the children, didn't want to part with the children, because they got used to them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But some people managed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I actually met one survivor from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I met her in Johannesburg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And her father went back to Lithuania, to the [NON-ENGLISH], or the village, and with some tricks he got his daughter out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she came to South Africa, and she survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But a lot of children were handed over to the non-Jewish people who say they'll look after them, they'll fed them, they'll clothe them, for money, for everything.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The next day, they gave them over to the Germans, and the children were liquidated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because the-- the Christian people were not good to the-- the civilian population of Lithuania, the Lithuanians themselves, were a very bad nation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Although, I, by myself, this is my opinion.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I can't judge people, but that's what I think in my mind.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
